SCR enhance circuit 12 is, for example, a PNP bipolar transistor 28 having an emitter connected to input 19, a base connected to input 21, and a collector connected to output 22. Preferably, the current gain (β
28
) of PNP bipolar transistor 28 is greater than the current gain (β
23
) of PNP bipolar transistor 23. It should be noted that the base of a bipolar transistor is referred to as the control electrode and the collector and emitter are referred to as current carrying electrodes. It should also be noted that a transistor is also referred to as an active device.
